Implemented a more robust version of warbo-guess-pi-buffer that:

1. First searches through existing pi-coding-agent buffers and matches by comparing their default-directory (expanded) with the current session directory
2. Falls back to generating the buffer name the same way pi-coding-agent does (using project-root or default-directory, then abbreviate-file-name)

This now tolerates differences like ~/foo vs /home/me/foo and matches exactly how pi-coding-agent creates buffer names. The function now returns a buffer object (or nil) instead of a buffer name string, and all calling functions have been updated accordingly.
